ADO-EKITI â€“ The rector, Federal Polytechnic, Ado-Ekiti, Dr. Hephzibar Oladebeye, has commended the Senior Special Assistant to Governor Fayemi on Public Building and Infrastructures, Wale Ajayi, for donating books and instructional materials to the institution. Oladebeye, spoke in Ado-Ekiti on Saturday while receiving books and instructional materials worth millions of naira donated to the School of Environmental Studies, Describing the donations as a good development, Oladebeye noted that the gesture would go a long way in complementing the efforts of the government in making the institution rank best in technical education in the country. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network Ajayi said the donation was a fulfilment of the second cardinal programme of Dr Kayode Fayemi, which centred on knowledge economy and amplified the need for public-private partnership for the uplift of education in the state. He applauded the management of the institution for the opportunity given him to serve in the institution, noting that the knowledge he gained while lecturing manifested in his political career. He said the donation was part of his contribution towards the development of the institution and to pay back to the polytechnic community that had given him enough knowledge. Oladebeye said acquisition of skills remained the greatest antidote to unemployment and insecurity caused by youth restiveness and other forms of crimes in Nigerian society.